<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Extenuate" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Extenuate,</orth> 1) to palliate (opposed to aggravate): <bibl n="shak. ven 1010" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1010</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.187" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.342" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 342</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 125</bibl>.<lb />2) to mitigate: <emph>which</emph> (law) <cit><quote>by no means we may e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 120</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) to undervalue, to detract from: <cit><quote>his glory not --d,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 42</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>